-- Intesa Sanpaolo to Acquire 51% Stake in Monte Parma for 159 Million Euros
-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2010-10-15T18:23:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/intesa-sanpaolo-to-acquire-51-stake-in-monte-parma-for-159-million-euros.html
Intesa Sanpaolo SpA , Italy’s second-
biggest-bank, agreed to buy a 51 percent in Banca Monte Parma
SpA from Fondazione Monte Parma for 159 million euros ($223
million).  Intesa also agreed to participate in a capital increase by
Monte Parma by acquiring 51 percent of the company’s planned 75
million euro share issuance, the lender said in a statement
today.  The Milan-based bank may increase its stake in Monte Parma
up to 79 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Sonia Sirletti  in Milan at 
